    "description": {
      "value": "<p>This technique is an advanced version of Raimeiken, and carries the same limitations as it does. However, instead of enhancing your next attack, you fire a ray of lightning at the target, which deals 4d6 electric damage on hit. If the target is soaking wet or wearing a lot of metal, it is @Condition[stunned]{stunned} for 1d3 rounds (Fortitude negates).<br><br>If the target is possessed by a spell, technique or ability, you may choose to damage the creature pos-sessing it instead. If you do, the target is automatically stunned (as above), without gaining a chance to save against it.</p>\n\n<hr><p><b>Empower:</b> Spend 2 Chakra to increase the damage by 1d6, up to 10d6 total.</p>\n<p><b>Mastery:</b> This technique's mastery is identical to Raimeiken's. The mastery of this technique also affects Raimeiken, and vice versa.</p>\n",
      "summary": "",
      "instructions": ""
    },
